The paper deals with the construction of graph spanners, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various areas of computer science. The congested clique model is a well-studied model for distributed computing, and the paper presents new algorithms for spanner construction in this model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization, which suggest cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with network optimization, which suggests cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) as another possible category.
